INSERT INTO `questions_and_answers` (`id`, `learning_cycle`, `material`, `material_title`, `lesson_video`, `question`, `answer`, `option_1`, `option_2`, `option_3`) VALUES
(1, 1, '<p>\nThe internet has come a long way, from static web pages to social media and smart apps. Now, we are entering a new era called Web3, and it‚Äôs changing the internet as we know it. But what exactly is Web3?\nWeb3 (short for Web 3.0) is the next generation of the internet that aims to decentralize control from big tech companies and give more power, ownership, and privacy back to users. It is built using blockchain technology, cryptography, and decentralized protocols.\n</p>\n\n<br>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"quickbox\">\n     <b class=\"ideabulb\">&#128161;</b>  I‚Äôm sure  ‚Äúblockchain‚Äù, ‚Äúcryptography‚Äù, and ‚Äúdecentralized protocols‚Äù sounds even bigger and confusing than ‚ÄúWeb3‚Äù , but that‚Äôs exactly why you are here and should stick around for longer. </p>\n</p>\n\n\n<br>\nSimply put, Web3 is the ‚Äúdecentralized internet‚Äù. It‚Äôs built using blockchain technology and is designed to give more control to users instead of big companies like Google, Facebook, or Amazon. With Web3, users can own their data, manage digital assets like cryptocurrencies, and interact online without needing to trust‚Äîor depend on‚Äîcentral authorities.\n\n\n<br><br>\n\n<p>\n <h3><b>A Quick History</b></h3> \nTo understand Web3, it helps to look at what came before it:\n\n<ul>\n    <li>Web1 (1990s‚Äìearly 2000s): The ‚Äúread-only‚Äù internet. You could visit websites, but couldn‚Äôt interact much.\n</li>\n    <li>Web2 (2000s‚Äìnow): The ‚Äúread-and-write‚Äù internet. Social media, cloud apps, and e-commerce grew. But it also meant companies started collecting and controlling huge amounts of user data.\n</li>\n    <li>Web3: The ‚Äúread-write-own‚Äù internet. It‚Äôs about user control, decentralization, and digital ownership.\n</li>\n</ul>\n</p>\n<br><br>\n\n<p> \n<h3><b> Key Features of Web3</b></h3>\n\n<ol>\n    <li>\n        <b>Decentralization</b>\n        No single company or entity controls the entire network. Instead, it‚Äôs run by many independent nodes (computers) around the world.\n    </li>\n    \n\n    <li>\n        Web3 apps (called dApps) run on peer-to-peer networks like blockchains, not on centralized servers. This means no single company owns or controls the app or its data.\n\n    </li>\n\n    <li>\n     <b> Digital Ownership :</b>In Web3, you can own digital items‚Äîlike art, music, or game items‚Äîthrough tools like NFTs (Non-Fungible Tokens). You store them in a crypto wallet, which only you control.\n    </li>\n\n\n    <li>\n        <b>Built-in Money System:</b>Web3 uses cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin and Ethereum to send money instantly‚Äîwithout banks, middlemen, or borders.\n         [This is the dominant aspect of web3 and have generated significant interest of technological investors and enthusiasts.] \n    </li>\n\n    <li>\n        <b>Smart Contracts:</b>\n        These are self-executing codes on the blockchain that run automatically when conditions are met. For example, a smart contract could release payment only when a job is completed‚Äîno human needed.\n    </li>\n\n    <li>\n        <b>Open Source:</b>Most Web3 projects are open source, meaning anyone can see, use, or improve the code. This encourages collaboration and innovation.\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <b>Interoperability:</b>Web3 apps can work together easily. For example, you can use your crypto wallet to buy an NFT on one platform and then use it in a game on another platform.\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <b>Permissionless:</b>Anyone can join and use Web3 without needing permission from a central authority. You don‚Äôt need to create an account or get approved by a company.\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <b>Transparency:</b>All transactions and data on the blockchain are visible to everyone. This means you can verify what‚Äôs happening without needing to trust a company.\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <b>Community Governance:</b>Many Web3 projects are governed by their users through decentralized autonomous organizations (DAOs). This means decisions are made collectively, not by a single company.\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <b>Privacy and Identity:</b>Web3 uses your crypto wallet as your identity. You control what information to share, and there are no passwords to remember.\n    </li>\n\n</ol>\n</p>\n<br><br>\n\n<p> \n<h3><b> Real-Life Examples</b></h3>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        Crypto wallets like MetaMask let you buy, store, and use cryptocurrencies or NFTs.\n    </li>\n    <li>Decentralized apps like Uniswap let you swap tokens without a bank or exchange.\n</li>\n    <li>NFT marketplaces like OpenSea let you create, buy, or sell digital art that you truly own.\n</li>\n    <li>Decentralized games let you own in-game items and even earn money from playing.\n</li>\n</ul>\n</p>\n<br><br>\n\n<p>     \n    <h3><b>Why Should You Care? </b></h3>\n\n    <ul>\n        <li>\nTechnological developments is constant and thus every individual is expected to grow along or be left behind.\nWeb3 protects your privacy and identity, and gives you ownership of your digital life.</li>\n        <li>\nOffers financial freedom through crypto tools, and investments when properly done.</li>\n        <li>\nOpens up opportunities to earn, build, and participate in global communities‚Äîno matter where you live; It literally solves the problem of international payments, \nso you can easily pay and access services in another country from wherever you are.</li>\n    </ul>\n</p>\n<br><br>\n\n<p> \n<h3><b>What Are the Challenges?</b></h3> \n\nWeb3 is still young. Some problems you might face:\n<ul>\n    <li>It can be confusing at first (wallets, gas fees, keys, etc.)‚Ä¶.This is exactly why we are here.\n</li>\n    <li>Some DApps are hard to use.\n</li>\n    <li>Scams and mistakes can be costly\n</li>\n    <li>Governments are still figuring out how to regulate it.\n</li>\n</ul>\n</p>\n<br><br>\n\n<p> \n   But just like the early days of the internet, Web3 is growing fast, and people who learn early will benefit while helping shape the future; So if you\'re curious and ready to explore, Welcome once again.\n</p>', 'Web3 overview', 'hfg', 'What is the main goal of Web3?', 'To decentralize control and give users more power and privacy', 'To make internet faster', 'To increase ad revenue', 'To promote social media usage'),
